1 0 0 1 54 579.00 Tm
(  - 128 GB Toshiba NAND) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 566.00 Tm
(  - 4096-byte block size) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 553.00 Tm
(  - GPT/APFS container at disk0s1) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 535.00 Tm
(The first block of /dev/rdisk0 reads successfully and contains a GPT protective MBR) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 522.00 Tm
(ending in 55 aa.) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 496.00 Tm
(Why Linux does not see the iPhone storage yet) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 470.00 Tm
(The Hoolock Linux boot only shows RAM disks \(/dev/ram0 through /dev/ram15\). That means) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 457.00 Tm
(Linux is not reaching the internal NAND as a block device at all.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 439.00 Tm
(This is not an APFS format problem yet. APFS only matters after Linux has a real block) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 426.00 Tm
(device like /dev/sda, /dev/mmcblk0, or an Apple NAND equivalent. Right now it has no) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 413.00 Tm
(internal storage block device.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 395.00 Tm
(The iPhone 6 Plus storage path is:) Tj
