/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 258.00 Tm
(  - ans@8040000) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 245.00 Tm
(  - compatible: iop,s5l8960x) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 232.00 Tm
(  - role: ANS) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 219.00 Tm
(  - interrupts: 0x25, 0x24, 0x27, 0x26) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 206.00 Tm
(  - register region: address 0x208040000, length 0x2000) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 193.00 Tm
(  - nub compatible: iop-nub,rtbuddy) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 167.00 Tm
(What does not solve it) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 141.00 Tm
(  - A generic Android GSI by itself does not make the storage appear.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 128.00 Tm
(  - The supplied recovery.img is a Qualcomm Android boot image, so its kernel is not) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 115.00 Tm
(  bootable on Apple A8. Its ramdisk/userspace can be useful, but the kernel must still) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 102.00 Tm
(  be the iPhone Linux kernel.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 89.00 Tm
(  - Enabling APFS support alone is not enough.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 76.00 Tm
(  - The existing CONFIG_NVME_APPLE=y path is for newer Apple ANS/NVMe controllers, not) Tj
